Jeff Wicks, News24Four people have been killed and three critically injured when a taxi collided with a car. (Netcare 911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - Four people were killed and three critically injured when a taxi collided with a car on the N4 near Solomon Mahlangu drive in Pretoria on Friday afternoon.Paramedics declared two men and two women dead at the scene, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said.A helicopter was used to airlift one of the inured, a child, to a trauma unit in Johannesburg.With heavy traffic as a result of the accident, motorists were advised to use alternative routes.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.